text: Corte Madera (; formerly Adams) is an incorporated town in Marin County, California, United States. The population was 10,222 at the 2020 census. Corte Madera is about south of San Rafael. In Spanish, Corte Madera means "chopped wood". The area was famous for producing lumber out of redwood trees which went into the construction of the city of San Francisco. == References == == Other websites == * Official City of Corte Madera website * Corte Madera Library Category:1878 establishments in California Category:Settlements in Marin County, California Category:Towns in California Category:Cities in the San Francisco Bay Area
